---
import ScenariosLayout from '../../layouts/ScenariosLayout.astro';
---

<ScenariosLayout
  title="Gap Dynamics — VegaReady Scenario Analysis"
  description="Supply disruption → substitution → oversupply cycles. Who fills the gap, what happens when the original supply returns, and how competitive landscapes shift permanently."
  section="Gap Dynamics"
>
  <div class="label">Gap dynamics</div>
  <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 1rem;">What happens when<br/>the gap reopens.</h1>
  <p style="font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 3rem;">Every disruption triggers substitution. Every substitution creates new dependencies. When the original supply returns, the competitive landscape has changed. Understanding this cycle is how you position for both the crisis and the recovery.</p>

  <div style="text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px;">
    <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-size: 28px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 12px;">&nu;</div>
    <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Gap analysis in development</div>
    <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 400px; margin: 0 auto 16px; line-height: 1.6;">Commodity-by-commodity substitution analysis with ramp timelines, contract structures, oversupply risk quantification, and post-crisis competitive landscape projections.</p>
    <a href="/scenarios" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--cyan); font-weight: 600;">View cascade framework &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</ScenariosLayout>

<style>
  .label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--cyan); letter-spacing: 3px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 16px; }
</style>
